%%pyspark
blob_account_name = "pandemicdatalake"
blob_container_name = "public"
blob_relative_path = "curated/covid-19/bing_covid-19_data/latest/bing_covid-19_data.parquet"
blob_sas_token = r""
# Allow SPARK to read from Blob remotely
wasbs_path = 'wasbs://%s@%s.blob.core.windows.net/%s' % (blob_container_name, blob_account_name, blob_relative_path)

spark.conf.set(
    'fs.azure.sas.%s.%s.blob.core.windows.net' % (blob_container_name, blob_account_name),
    blob_sas_token)
df = spark.read.parquet(wasbs_path)
display(df.limit(10))

from pyspark.sql import functions as f
df.select(f.countDistinct("country_region")).show(truncate=False)
df.select("country_region").distinct().collect()
display(df.filter(df.country_region=="Sweden").select("updated", "confirmed"))
df.filter(df.country_region=="Sweden").select(f.max("updated"), f.max("deaths")).show()
df.where(df.updated=='2021-05-07').select(f.count("id")).show()
display(df.select("country_region").distinct().orderBy(df.country_region.asc()))
display((spark.sql("select distinct country_region from cov order by country_region limit 4")))

from pyspark.sql.functions import udf
from pyspark.sql.types import StringType
def getThree(str):
    return str[0:3]

threeUdf = udf(lambda x: getThree(x), StringType())

df.select(threeUdf(df.country_region)).show()

display(spark.sql("select country_region, round((avg(deaths)/avg(confirmed)), 4) as dt from cov group by country_region  having dt > 0.07 order by dt desc"))
display(spark.sql("select cast(load_time as date) from cov limit 4"))
countries = spark.sql("select distinct iso2, country_region from cov order by iso2 asc")
